caption: Best food and nice service 🥰,
Jai was super helpful when we came in for lunch! He was very informative. Service was great. Highly recommended!!
My go to place whenever i want south indian food.  I've tried the other curries, but they weren't quite as good as the south indian food they have.  The sambhar and Rasam are amazing!

Mild 2 Spicy had a great environment and fantastic food. The service was also wonderful, super helpful and friendly. Overall it was a great experience and I highly recommended everyone to go try this place out!!
The place had the perfect ambience with the excellent staff. Loved the way staff members interacted with us . The food was really tasty with great quantity. Would definitely visit again .

Just enjoyed a great lunch there with my family, some of whom were trying Indian food for the first time. Everything was delicious and there was plenty for us to share and sample different dishes. We also had food left over. Food and drinks were reasonably priced, great atmosphere, and the servers were friendly and helpful describing dishes and making suggestions. Looking forward to our next visit!
His place has amazing, feel-good, take-home dishes. I'm in process of trying every curry on the menu! Highly recommend the veggie samosas, you can't go wrong.

I love indian food and am new to chicago. My friend suggested this place for chicken tikka masala and butter chicken. The taste of the dishes seems to be like eating marinara sauce with more than 70 percent tomato flavor. Also the white rice that I got with the food was almost dry and stinking.

Food-wise, the portion is HUGE! The naan is probably the size of my torso! I like the butter chicken the most, the sauce is good and the meat is juicy. Chicken tikka seems to be a more salty but less flavor version of butter chicken to me, and the meat is drier. Each entry comes with a giant portion of rice, so no need to get extra rice as I did.

Very solid Indian restaurant with a wide variety of options. On this visit, I tried both the garlic naan and chicken vindaloo. The naan was stellar and you get a ton. The vindaloo was very solid paired with well-cooked rice. It was just the right amount of spicy. It could have packed a bit more "full" flavor into the chicken, but that's nitpicking a bit. Regardless, this is a place where you are unlikely to leave disappointed.
The food was fresh, but somewhat on the blander side for my liking. The wait staff was friendly.
Everything was packaged well and arrived very warm! Overall, I don't think the curry or Naan was anything too special, but I feel that it is still of great value. Fair pricing and good portions.

I have ordered biryani here for multiple times. Recently I have seen raitha which is given with biryani being watery and thin with no proper taste.  I will reconsider my rating if see the improvement.
Superb atmosphere, great service, friendly staff with a large menu choice and delicious meals.

I have ordered delivery from here multiple times and each time the food is still hot and delicious. The food is packed well so it stays hot and doesn't spill. I ordered a Mysore masala dosa, paneer makhani, onion kulcha, aloo chaat, and ras malai. The food is delicious and very well packed. The portion sizes are amazingly great for leftovers. I love how the dishes came with rice as well without an extra charge.
Their gaélico naans seems to be substandard and tikka masala Was not hot for a pick Up order. Totally disappointed

I got saag paneer, malai kofta, and paneer makhani. The paneer makhani was new to me, and perhaps my favorite, though all three were delicious. I'm not joking when I tell you this plus naan made 8 meals!  They definitely give you nice portions for the cost, so you really feel you get your money's worth.
Excellent customer service, in particular Jai. Has an extensive menu with a wide range of options.

I just moved to the area and found this place close by!   Such a comfortable place to sit and relax while enjoying the amazing food they have. Having Jay as a server was quite nice as well! His customer service skills are on point!

Portions are very generous especially for the price and they are serious about their spice level if you request it. Takeout direct to them also comes with a 20% discount. Really flavorful Indian food and one of our go tos when ordering.
Great
I love the food here. There's a cool inclination here - the climate of Mild 2 Spicy is exceptionally enamoring. I appreciate investing energy here. I come here routinely.

Fantastic Indian restaurant.  Expansive menu, separate Vegan and Gluten free menus along with a surprisingly interesting drink menu with creative cocktails.  Staff was exceedingly helpful, polite, professional and distancing.  Happily helped with ordering and answering questions about the menu  Food was delicious, not overly seasoned and plentiful.  Will definitely be going back soon

Mild 2 Spicy have the chief flavorful Indian food! I incline toward the soup, naan, and barbecue here. I truly like the spot for their cordial attitude. I'm an every day client here and that I choose to come.
bad service they don't care about their customers

I never leave reviews, but this restaurant is amazing. The food is to die for, the portions are huge, and the service is at another level. Our waiter, Prateek,was the sweetest, nicest, most accommodating person ever. We will be back for sure!

Totally unprofessional, had worst of the experience service staff, seems to be like not careful about their customers also the dining setup was already placed which is totally unethical in this pendemic and also unsafe we were group of 10 and we are never getting back in there!!!!! They need to be improved other wise there's no way to run a business like this when can't take care of the customer!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

I loved ordering from this place and the experience has been excellent until recently. Their naan used to be soft and fluffy and now it tastes chewy and hard to break. We ordered samosa, malai kofta and kadai paneer yesterday and all the items were below average. Samosas were oily and the filling was crumbly and didn’t taste fresh at all.  Kadai paneer had mostly onions and few pieces of panner and other veggies. Malai koftas were as hard as rocks. They were obviously frozen beforehand and not properly defrosted before being served.  These food items are pretty expensive and the quality can’t be simply ignored.
delicious food!

I ordered a full takeout meal, which included Goat Korma, Rasam (soup), & Garlic naan. Overall, the quality and flavor was good but I’ve had better and paid less for it.  I’m giving two stars instead of four because of the Goat Korma. It tasted good. However, a third of what was supposed to be chunks of goat meat were actually chunks of bone. Most of the meat chunks I was given had small bone fragments in them. I could have easily broken a tooth eating there.
Very nice Indian food. Mysore masala dosa is the best
This restaurant gives you a delightful Indian food experience! The first place I always visit when I’m in Chicago.
I think it’s one of the best Indian restaurant. I’ve been to most of the restaurants on Devon street and I travel all over the US. Hands down these guys are the best!

This place is soooooooo amazing! I have never felt more satisfied with flavors in my meal. The fact that I can guiltlessly eat a hearty vegetarian meal that actually satisfies blows me away. I will forever be a fan!

looking forward to coming back with my relatives. prices are decent.

Mutter paneer was fabulous. Chicken vindaloo is so awesomely and insanely spicy. Samosa chat is like Indian lasagna. Highly recommend, look forward to ordering again.
The Veggie Samosas were amazing and the guy in the front Vik is super friendly 👍👍

Mild 2 Spicy has been my favorite new restaurant I started ordering from regularly during the pandemic. The chicken vindaloo with garlic naan is my go-to, but everything I’ve ordered has been flavorful, delicious, and arrived hot like it was straight from the kitchen. Bonus points for huge portions that make for tasty leftovers!
A clean and organized place with plenty of seating that is perfect for the Indian Buffet Weekend Party. The staff was attentive:-)
Absolutely incredible Indian place, service was just outstanding and the food was reasonably priced, big portions, and delicious!

The food was delicious. We ordered butter chicken, chicken tikka masala, cheese masala dosa, and garlic naan. We really appreciated that the restaurant was on top of it, and they made sure our new order was ready really fast. We will be ordering from here again! 5 stars!

We have been here twice and loved the food both times. You will fall in love with the chicken vindaloo!  Seriously, even the medium spicy one.  Naan and kofta were great, and the slightly sweeter kofta helped us eat the vindaloo.
Had a very pleasant experience here. The staff is very friendly and attentive. The food is delicious. I'd recommend this place if you want to introduce your new friends to Indian food.
Everything was inexpensive relative to other Indian places in the area. The samosa was so delicious. The chicken vindaloo was very spicy just the way I prefer. Definitely will reorder again.

So the first time i ate here it was incredible food. This time i received food togo and the samosas were straight mushy potatoes. So gross.  I really did not like the chicken vindaloo at all. I ordered it at a medium spice which was good, but the chicken chunks were WAY too big to really enjoy meal and the rice served with it was cold.
Never disappoints!
My favorite Indian spot in Chicago. I recommend Chicken Tikka Masala.
I am so happy with the food and service. To my knowledge, they are the only place that brings not only naan to your table but also small dada dosas!!
A much healthier version of the classic vegetarian dish. Delivery is always on time, dishes are super flavourful, and portions are generous.
Must try
Really good Indian food.  Portions are gigantic. Highly recommend the curry and garlic naan.
The chicken vindaloo Is fantastic even with its intense spice level, and make sure you always get the Nan! 👍🏽
Very good and very spicy. I always get vindaloo curry plates
Great little Indian spot with cute decoration. Ordered the chicken tikka masala which was very delicious. Also ordered the garlic naan which was amazing. Highly recommend.

Consistently delicious Indian delivery food. The chicken tikka masala has the perfect spice and the garlic naan is perfectly cooked. We also typically get the Veggie Biryani, which has a great spice level. would not hesitate to order from here again!
The food is so good and very well spiced. The chef is from southern India so he knows how to add some real heat if that's your thing. the staff is lovely!
Best Indian food I've personally had. It's so impressive I find myself coming back regularly. I could literally eat here very often. The service is always super friendly and attentive. Great place.
My favorite spot! I get their lamb Biryani and it's cooked perfectly and is spicy!

Tasty! Garlic naan was perfect combination of crispy outside and soft fluffy middle. The entrees we got were spicy enough to give a good kick but not spicy enough to detract from the flavor. Portions were large and definitely enough for plenty of leftovers.
Best Indian in Chicago! I've tried a bunch of places and this is head and shoulders above the others. Nice service too.
The best tandoori chicken I've ever tasted! Best papadums I've ever tasted too, nice service, reasonable cost. I'm highly impressed.
I love Indian food and have eaten at fine Indian restaurants all over the country.  I'm impressed with this place.
I was on the hunt for a great Indian food restaurant besides cumin in wicker park and I've found it!! This place never disappoints!!!
Some of the best Indian food available. I live 25-30 min away but it's worth it to get it delivered! Some of the best vindaloo around.

Absolutely phenomenal!  The fried kale chat appetizer is out of this world and their sauces are so flavorful.  The portion sizes are more than enough for multiple meals. Great prices honestly best Indian food around.

Updated on 9/11/2020:  This used to be our go-to spot for Indian takeout. After a craving for this food once the weather cooled off a bit, we decided to order the usual suspects to find out that the price had increased on our order by over $8 for the same dishes.  Upon dining, the food was incredibly bland and not anywhere near the quality that we had experienced a few months ago. There was nothing special or remotely similar to the delicious food we have experienced here in the many visits in the past which was quite disappointing. I completely understand price increases in this time, but that in combination with the reduced quality of the food will likely mean that we search for another go-to spot. I hope this was a one off scenario, but in reading recent reviews it seems that this has been occurring much more frequently as of late.

Below is my order: - Malai Kofta (Medium) - Mixed Vegetable Curry (Medium) - Garlic Naan - Mango Lassi  The Kofta was really salty. The Vegetable Curry was ok, it was just tomatoes and onions crushed up together with some red chili powder. I cook a lot of Indian food, so I could tell that they had just thrown random spices in there. The Garlic Naan was hard and tasted bitter bc the garlic pieces were either burned/ stale. The Mango Lassi was on the sweeter side, but good enough. After eating just a little bit of this  dinner, I had a TERRIBLE stomach ache. I tried it again the following day and the same result. I wonder if it’s the Amchur/Chat Masala spices they seem to use as their curry base?  The only reason I give 2 stars is for: 1) Quick delivery time for Indian food (30 mins) 2) Big proportions, with lots left over for 2 more servings
Came in on a Weds. I will be back with my relatives. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.

The staff is amazing, even during covid they are cheery and accommodating  We dined in and would do so again, but we may also have a new Indian take-out favorite.

If you want Americanized (i.e. bland and flavorless) Indian food then there are tons of Indian restaurants to suit your needs. Now, if you want the taste of exotic spices and flavors that will make you think that you are sitting at a Indian restaurant in New Delhi, then Mild 2 Spicy is the place for you. The curries are delicious, and you can adjust your heat level, without sacrificing spice and flavor. My son can't handle any heat in his food, and he devoured his mild Chicken Tikka Masala. I, on the other hand, love spice and heat. I ordered a Chicken Vindaloo that made me cry with joy and heat with every bite. It wasn't like they just added more chili powder to make it spicy, they somehow balanced the extra heat and the spices to create a party in my mouth.  Another thing that this restaurant does, and other cheap out on, is give you delicious fragrant basmati rice with your meal, without charging extra. How can you eat a Indian curry without rice? To complete the dinner, they have an amazing selection of Indian breads from naan to paratha, puris and rotis.  One thing I must mention, is that you have to try the Pani Puri cocktail. It's a delight of spice, salt, sour and sweet in a delicious drink. I will warn you, that just one will not be enough.  The prices here are very reasonable, and the portion sizes pretty much guarantees that you will have enough for lunch the next day.  Dang it, now I'm hungry just think about the food. I guess I know where I'm going this weekend!

I've had Indian frozen dinners that tasted better than what they serve here.  We had 2 orders of Keema Somosa. The naan, Chicken Tikka Masala, Saag Paneer, and Paneer Makhani were absolutely tasteless.  It was as if they used Ragu sauce to base their gravy.
